- 'Best rank' and 'worst rank' refer to the highest and lowest performance ranks within the same city, respectively;
- The results are ordered by the best rank, so the team with the best performance appears first.

- The win percentage is calculated as (total wins / (total wins + total losses + total ties)) * 100;
- The query includes data on ticket sales and revenue, which can provide insights into the financial health of the teams;
- The teams are ranked based on their win percentage, with the highest win percentages appearing first.

